  "text": "In summary, [CITATION_1] generalizations concerning the allometry of the DGC appear to be upheld for another group of insects, thus lending weight to the validity of his generalizations. Likewise, his conclusion that similar scaling exponents for CO 2 emission volumes, and for , result in the indeVco 2 pendence of DGC frequency from body mass in insects also appears to be more widely applicable than the original, single study of tenebrionid beetles (Lighton 1991) would perhaps have suggested. In this study, although DGC frequency was margin- ally significant across all phases, the coefficient of determination of the relationship was low (12%), suggesting that if it exists at all, the relationship is weak. Thus, we have been unable to disprove the first of our major hypotheses.",
